  "bio": [
    "Deepinder Goyal cofounded food delivery service Zomato in 2008 which became Eternal in 2024.",
    "Zomato's IPO in 2021 was oversubscribed 35 times and it listed at a valuation of $12 billion.",
    "In 2022, Zomato acquired quick commerce platform Blinkit. It competes with rival Swiggy's Instamart.",
    "In January 2026 he resigned as CEO of flagship Eternal and became vice chairman. He said in a letter to the stock exchange that it was to pursue new ideas.",
    "In February 2026, Goyal's startup Temple, which is developing a wearable device  for measuring cerebral blood flow, got a $54 million investment from investors including Peak XV Partners and Steadview Capital."
  ],
  "about": [
    "Goyal has a math and computing degree from the premier Indian Institute of Technology in Delhi.",
    "Goyal was working with Bain & Company as a management consultant before he struck out on his own.",
    "In late 2025, he made a series of social media statements defending the gig economy even as delivery personnel went on a nationwide strike on New Year's eve."
